member.example:
This sample shows how to display the thumbnails of one previous loaded image in ImgEdit component.

              ImgThumbnails1.ImgEditComponent = ImgEdit1
              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150)
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails()

              ImgThumbnails1.ImgEditComponent = ImgEdit1;
              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150);
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails();

This sample shows how to load and display the thumbnails of one image bitmap object.

              Dim bmp As New System.Drawing.Bitmap("C:\Test.tif")
              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150)
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails(bmp)

              System.Drawing.Bitmap bmp = new System.Drawing.Bitmap("C:\\Test.tif");
              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150);
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails(bmp);

This sample shows how to load and display the thumbnails of one image byte array object.

             Dim m_ImageByteArray As Byte() = File.ReadAllBytes("C:\Test.tif")
             ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150)
             ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails(m_ImageByteArray)

             byte[] m_ImageByteArray = File.ReadAllBytes("C:\Test.tif");
             ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150);
             ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails(m_ImageByteArray);

This sample shows how to load and display the thumbnails of one image uri.

              Dim m_Uri as New Uri("http://www.imagecomponents.net/Images/Test.tif")
              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150)
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails(m_Uri)

              Uri m_uri = new Uri("http://www.imagecomponents.net/Images/Test.tif");
              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150);
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails(m_uri);

This sample shows how to load and display the thumbnails of one specified directory.

              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150)
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails("C:\MyImages\")

              ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150);
              ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails("C:\\MyImages\\");

This sample shows how to load and display the thumbnails of .jpg files from one specified directory.

               ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150)
               ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails("C:\MyImages\")

               ImgThumbnails1.ThumbnailSize = New System.Windows.Size(100, 150);
               ImgThumbnails1.LoadThumbnails("C:\\MyImages\\", ".jpg");

The following example refreshes the image thumbnail display of the first page.

             ImgThumbnails1.ImgThumbnailsRefresh()

             ImgThumbnails1.ImgThumbnailsRefresh();

The following example refreshes the image thumbnail display of the first page.

             ImgThumbnails1.ImgThumbnailsRefresh(0)

             ImgThumbnails1.ImgThumbnailsRefresh(0);

The following example closes the displayed image thumbnails.

              ImgThumbnails1.Close()

              ImgThumbnails1.Close();
